rComments: he's kind, but his lectures can be very vague and definitely do not include all the information that you'll be tested on, so read the textbook. the assignments are super easy which is nice. he mentions a lot of information in class that is not at all on the slides, so attend the lectures.

Midterms were solely out of a test bank and half of the time it had nothing to do with what we learned. Assignments are an easy A+ even with minimal effort. Lectures are long and boring and if he finds himself short in time, he goes through them super quickly and omits important details

The midterm was 40%, finals 50% and assignments 10%. He asks very specific questions from the textbook so read thoroughly, focus on echo360 questions as well because some of the questions were on midterms and finals

Textbook is expensive so buy used. Its a must for the final esp as the slides do not contain a lot of info and sometimes he skips over things. He explains most but if u want to make sure to do well or don't want to go to class, study the chapters in txt. Assignments are short and lack instructions, they aren't worth much so dw! Hes nice+lil boring
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Great prof.!Read the textbook and you'll be fine. Atiq really cares about his students' success and tries his best to make the course interesting .40% midterm, 50% final and 10% assignments (which are grade boosters). Such a nice man!Would totally recommend him for this course. Good luck!

Monotone, boring, & lacks communication with students. You're expected to know pretty much everything from the textbook (including random stats that are basically irrelevant to the course). I'm a straight A student, but I ended up with a way lower grade in this course. It wasn't the course that was the problem, it was this god-awful prof.
Hes really good if you attend classes, you defiantly need to take notes as some of the questions he gives in class are in the exam. Overall good prof.

Didn't go to class but read the all relevant chapters and reviewed his slides before and after.  There's a lot of information but the material isn't hard to understand, just takes time to get through it all. Dr. Rehman is lovely but for this class, I would stick with the text. As long as you keep up with reading, you should be fine for exams!

Such a sweet, kind professor.. he really cares about his students and their success. He answers questions well and will explain something many times if you need it. Don't hesitate to take a class with him!

Lectures are boring, monotone, and unstimulating. Exams are 100% textbook based (you can find the textbook PDF online). His slides don't have all the info so the book is useful. 1 midterm, 1 final - each worth 50%.  He does exam-style practice questions during class which are good.

Quiet, mumbles, difficult accent, monotone. Understanding what he's trying to say is hard. He says the textbook isn't mandatory but his slides contain almost no information, so you really gotta read it, man. 50% midterm + 50% finalterrible class. Take this course with someone else. Please.

Prof seemed to be very knowledgeable in the course material, but wasn't very good at transmitting in an enriching way. Dry lectures, spoke very quietly - was sometimes hard to understand. Midterms and exams seemed to be based out of a test bank. Lacked creativity in his teaching methods.

Nice professor - obviously cares if his students pass. Asks for feedback on midterms and asked the class what kind of midterms the qanted (MCQ vs. short answer). He has a thick accent and difficult to understand. There were things he brough up in class directly on the exam. Read the textbook and follow the slides and you will do well. Easy final.

He is very very nice and let you have input on the number of questions on exams. Multiple choice exams, random questions based on minute details from the textbook. Mumbles the entire class and rushes through material. Avoid this prof at all costs if you want anything more than a B
